§ANNODRAFT[
§ -> Draft mode Focus: Capture any operational information (visual, text, audio), do not worry about  -Images as stills or as image series (Stop Motion Pictures) -images can be captured by webcam or inserted via the clipboard, e.g. using a snipping tool -images can be opened in the system default editor for graphical annotations -Text can be quickly written without regard for formatting or styling -One audio clip can be recorded per slide, which can be replayed in draft and refine tabs (Default microphone is used) -Audio clips and images can be selectively deleted from slides -slides can be added and deleted -Keywords can be added for different uses: --Relevant to the instructions ("Tags") --List of tools used in a slide's context --List of parts used, e.g. the parts added to the assembly in the context of a slide.  -> Refine mode Focus: Make the captured information presentable and include additional data -load the text from the Draft Tab into the rich text editor in the Refine Tab -listen to the recorded audio draft and tansfer the information to the text  -Add warnings and notices in the instruction text  -add tables in the instruction text as HTML (Alternatively, add tables as images) -Add format slides: Title Slide or Chapter Slide -Adjust the order of slides in the gallery  -Add additional chapters, e.g. "safety" or "troubleshooting" -More Tags of all categories can be added  -> View mode Focus: User-View of the manual. -only contains information relevant to the reader of the manual:  --Images  --The text as seen in the Refine Tab, but non-editable --Tags (non-editable)  -Search Slide tags (any combination of the three categories can be searched at one time)          
]ANNODRAFT§
